    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Breed of heavy draft horse characterized by a thick muscular neck, small head, powerful shoulders and quarters, short legs, and having a sorrel (chestnut) coloring with a lighter mane. It is an old breed descended from the Flemish 'great horse,' the medieval battle horse native to the Low Countries.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
